Key Match Events: Brennan Johnson scored the opening goal for Wales in the 11th minute.
Harry Wilson scored the second goal for Wales in the 29th minute.
Logi Tomasson scored for Iceland in the 69th minute.
Danny Ward scored an own goal in the 72nd minute, leading to Iceland's equalizer.
Post-Match Reflections: Wales, still unbeaten under Craig Bellamy after three games, are second in the group on five points, two behind leaders Turkey.
Iceland are third in the group with four points.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at Laugardalsvöllur in Reykjavik, Iceland.
